A minor update, but with a pretty cool feature.

READMORE

The main new feature is a simpler way to replace templates. In addition to the manual template replacement syntax (`Template.foo.replaces("bar")`), you can now simply add the `custom_` prefix to any existing template name and the replacement will be picked up automatically. 

For example, if you want to replace the `post_title` template, you can simply create a template named `custom_post_title`. Here's a short video that showcases the feature:

