If you prefer using another prefix, you can simply set the `Telescope.config.customPrefix` variable to something else. 

Note that up to now the recommended way of adding customizations was through packages, but since version 0.20 you can also put your code right in your regular app directories if you prefer (unless of course you intend to publish your code to Atmosphere).

### Security Fix

This update also fixes an issue with over-publishing the Settings collection's private properties. 